# System Design Document

## 1. Overview
Provide a high-level description of the system, its purpose, and main features.

## 2. Requirements

### 2.1 Functional Requirements
- List the core functionalities the system must provide.

### 2.2 Non-Functional Requirements
- Performance, scalability, reliability, security, etc.

## 3. Architecture

### 3.1 High-Level Architecture Diagram
(Insert diagram or describe the main components and their interactions.)

### 3.2 Components
- Describe each major component/module and its responsibilities.

## 4. Data Model
- Describe the main entities, their attributes, and relationships.

## 5. API Design
- List key APIs with endpoints, methods, request/response formats.

## 6. Scalability & Reliability
- Strategies for scaling (horizontal/vertical), load balancing, failover, etc.

## 7. Security
- Authentication, authorization, data protection, etc.

## 8. Deployment
- Deployment architecture, CI/CD, environments.

## 9. Monitoring & Logging
- Tools and strategies for monitoring, alerting, and logging.

## 10. Appendix
- Glossary, references, additional notes.



## 11. Future Enhancements
- Outline potential features or improvements for future releases.

## 12. Assumptions & Constraints
- List any assumptions made during design and known limitations or constraints.

